*-{根}-據[[CBS|CBS]]的消息指出，《疑犯追蹤》在得到近15年來所有劇情類試播集中最高評分<ref name="fastcompany">{{cite web |url=http://www.fastcompany.com/1781182/jonathan-nolan-person-of-interest-cbs-jj-abrams |last=Karlin |first=Susan |title='Person Of Interest' Creator Jonathan Nolan Isn't Paranoid--Or Is He? |publisher=Fast Company |date=2011-09-21 |accessdate=2011-09-24 |archive-date=2011-09-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110924061824/http://www.fastcompany.com/1781182/jonathan-nolan-person-of-interest-cbs-jj-abrams |dead-url=no }}</ref>，而一位CBS高層的形容本劇「不常見的極具瘋狂吸引力」後，促使電視台把十年來都在星期四播放的熱門影集《[[CSI犯罪現場|CSI犯罪現場]]》挪到星期三，把该時段空出來給《疑犯追蹤》。<ref name="washingtonpost">{{cite web |last=de Moraes |first=Lisa |url=http://www.washingtonpost.com/blogs/tv-column/post/upfronts-week-2011-cbs-moves-csi-to-wednesday-cancels-criminal-minds-spin-off/2011/05/17/AFYXLT6G_blog.html |title=Upfronts Week 2011: CBS moves ‘CSI’ to Wednesday to make room for new J.J. Abrams series |work=The TV Column |publisher=''[[The_Washington_Post|The Washington Post]]'' |date=2011-05-18 |accessdate=2011-09-24 |archive-date=2012-11-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121112112513/http://www.washingtonpost.com/blogs/tv-column/post/upfronts-week-2011-cbs-moves-csi-to-wednesday-cancels-criminal-minds-spin-off/2011/05/17/AFYXLT6G_blog.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>首播集不負所望地贏得播出時段的收視冠軍，吸引了1320萬的觀眾收看。<ref name="zap2it">{{cite web |first=Mikey |last=O'Connell |url=http://blog.zap2it.com/frominsidethebox/2011/09/tv-ratings-x-factor-holds-charlies-angels-off-to-modest-start.html |title=TV Ratings: 'X Factor' holds, 'Charlie's Angels' off to modest start |work=From Inside the Box |publisher=[[Zap2it|Zap2it]] |date=2011-09-23 |accessdate=2011-09-24 |archive-date=2011-09-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110924040845/http://blog.zap2it.com/frominsidethebox/2011/09/tv-ratings-x-factor-holds-charlies-angels-off-to-modest-start.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>
*《[[舊金山紀事報|舊金山紀事報]]》的執行編輯兼電視評論員大衛威根（David Wiegand）表示《疑犯追蹤》跳脫了噱頭包裝，不只是因為有非常細微地角色刻劃和劇情敘述，還因為本劇探討了後911時代觀眾的偏執感。<ref>{{cite news |author=David Wiegand |url=http://www.sfgate.com/cgi-bin/article.cgi?f=/c/a/2011/09/21/DDJ91L6HC3.DTL |title='Person of Interest' and 'Prime Suspect' reviews |work=[[San_Francisco_Chronicle|San Francisco Chronicle]] |date=2011-09-21 |page=E-1 |accessdate=2011-09-25 |archive-date=2011-09-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110924203113/http://www.sfgate.com/cgi-bin/article.cgi?f=%2Fc%2Fa%2F2011%2F09%2F21%2FDDJ91L6HC3.DTL |dead-url=no }}</ref> 
